The paper proposes a deep learning framework for clustering, which involves embedding and spectral clustering. The paper focuses on learning discriminative embeddings and clustering, which are important topics in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves using mutual information estimation, which is a common technique in natural language processing and information retrieval, suggesting that cs.CL (Computation and Language) could also be a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a dual autoencoder network, which is a type of neural network, indicating that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be a possible sub-category.
